##71-year-old in critical condition wants to give up, doctors make a bold decision

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Wenxiaoxiao, reporter of thepaper.cn, from Wuhan

Yuan Lingui, a 71-year-old Wuhan native, feels he is slowly recovering. Just over a month ago, doctors thought she was a long shot.

When he was hospitalized in early February, he Oxygenation only 76 percent (more than 95 percent of normal people) , and at one point as little as 50 percent, she said.

Chen Ailan, from the First Affiliated Hospital of the Guangzhou Medical University, was the leader of the medical team of the first medical team in Guangdong that assisted the Hankou Hospital in Wuhan, yuan Lingui is one of the patients under the joint responsibility of experts in Guangdong and Hubei.

After the onset, Yuan Lingui had felt "body acid and weakness, rough skin, crus to feet are stiff, in addition to drinking water, is a waste. ".

Now she can tell doctors that she no longer needs help washing her hair and bathing, and that she can last longer by breathing through a straw in a glass of water. However, she still faces some problems, such as the inability to fully deoxygenate, inability to chew, and difficult to squat while going to the toilet.

In any case, of all the critical care cases, yuan was one of the most exciting success stories, and was typically posted on Wechat's public account, headed by the Zhong Nanshan team.

Chen Ailan said that as early as late February, the elderly from critical to severe, and nucleic acid tests were negative for both times, but the lung function has not yet recovered, need to continue to receive rehabilitation treatment.

Yuan was glad he hadn't given up completely. Especially when she saw her son pull an all-nighter to care for and encourage himself: "If he was not so determined, I would have lost my life, and gave up. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Tried to give it up twice

Yuan now recalled that "the disease is too fast, there is no room for discussion. ".

On the evening of January 26(the second day of the Lunar New Year) , she felt sick to her stomach and began to vomit and have diarrhea. She felt cold all over and had low fever. Although no one knew at the time if she had the new coronavirus, the family was cautious and gave her a room to live in alone. It was the fourth day of the city's closure due to the new outbreak of pneumonia. Large hospitals were full, and people without obvious signs of pneumonia were advised to stay at home. No one knows how to deal with, Yuan Lingui took home years ago with the rush to buy even flower Qingwen, Oseltamivir, we all hope is only false alarm.

But on the third day of isolation (Jan. 29) , yuan stopped to breathe after just a few steps, her skin began to darken "like soy sauce, " and she began to panic and worry that she would die at home.

Son Gaojun immediately took Yuan Lingui to the Community Health Service Center, the other side advised him to go to the hospital for Ct.. The day's CT showed a double lung infection.

At Hankou Hospital in Wuhan, one of the first designated hospitals to treat new cases of pneumonia, Gao was stunned: The hospital was packed with people, and the transfusion hall was filled with recliners of all kinds that people brought with them.

Yuan Lingui started an IV in the infusion hall. But she felt more and more beat the spirit, can only drink water, what can not eat. "It was so hot and uncomfortable, it was like being thrown into a pancake oven, " she recalled. "My muscles were all flaccid and I couldn't move my feet. I felt like I was 'shot. ' " There were people crying all over the place, kneeling, standing, sitting, sleeping, all over the place.

On February 2, the third day of the infusion, yuan entered the emergency room. She climbed onto a chaise longue in the corridor of the emergency room and felt as if she would never get up.

At that time, the doctor just won an oxygen bottle for Yuan Lingui, Gao Jun did not dare to walk away: "An oxygen bottle would like a dozen people to rob. "

The scene of rescue room once let Yuan Lingui psychological collapse. At least, Gao recalled, "she was gone from side to side. ". After dark, Yuan began to hallucinate that there was a Flaming Mountains river in front of her, with Red Rivers at her feet. When she woke up, she was worried her brain was fried and she was thinking over and over. She compiled suicide notes on her phone and sent them to her family. Gaojun did not know how to respond, he almost collapsed, but on second thought, collapsed and what can be done?

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Around February 6, some light and ordinary patients in Hankou Hospital were transferred to other hospitals for treatment, leaving a part of the beds free. Yuan was finally allocated a bed in the inpatient ward. This means that Yuan can finally get systematic treatment and care, but she wants to give up again.

In her opinion, it had been nearly half a month since the onset of the disease, the feeling of body soreness was still strong, the chopsticks could not be picked up during the meal, the body was roasted like fire, the calves and feet were stiff, and the skin of the whole body was as rough as dead trees. Apart from being able to drink water, she felt like a "basket case" .

There is no absolute standard of treatment

Chen Ailan first contact Yuan Lingui, is the latter from the rescue room into the hospital ward. Yuan was suddenly sicker, breathing air when only 76% of the Oxygenation, and normal people's values can usually reach more than 95% .

After consultation and discussion, Chen Ailan, Guo Yabing, Xie Jiaxing, the first experts from the Guangdong Han medical team, as well as doctors from Hankou Hospital, Le Wenqing, Xu Ying and Yu Hao, decided to give her relatively large doses of hormone shock therapy, and exceeded the recommended dosage of the protocol.

It was a bold decision. According to Chen Ailan, the main reason for using hormones is to reduce the body's inflammatory response and to help people recover from the acute phase: "Just like a child walking, you just start holding his hand, and then let him go when he is stable. " But if the judgment is not accurate, causes the use time or the length is not right, then possibly appears the secondary bacterium infection, the blood sugar elevates, the FEMORAL head necrosis and so on bad condition.

Several of the experts involved in the discussion recalled the situation and congratulated themselves on seizing the best opportunity to use hormones.

"both of her lungs were white, like frosted glass, and the inflammation oozed out very clearly and very badly, " Chen recalled of Yuan's CT scan. "The team assessed and decided to increase the dose, or they would miss the best time for treatment. "

Dr. Xu Ying from Hankou is yuan's attending physician. She recalled that yuan was barely able to speak at the time, "too seriously ill, " and that the panel had hesitated about using relatively large doses of hormones, but ultimately decided to "take a chance. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
According to the then-experimental version of the fifth protocol, critical cases were advised to use steroids for 3-5 days, where appropriate, at a dose not exceeding 1-2 mg / kg / day of methylprednisolone, otherwise clearance of coronavirus could be easily delayed. In other words, Yuan should not take more than 100 mg of the hormone a day if he follows the guidelines.

According to the actual situation of Yuan Lingui, the group finally increased the dose to 160 mg per day, reduced to 80 MG after two days of continuous use, and gradually reduced to 20 MG, before and after about 10 days of hormone use.

With such an experience, chen Ailan deeply felt that there are still no universal standards for the treatment of critically ill patients with new pneumonia: "national experts can only sum up a relatively standardized diagnosis and treatment program, but this is only a rough principle. ". It's not that simple to be a doctor. If you can follow the guidelines and get better care, it's not new pneumonia, it's just pneumonia."

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Yuan's treatment process was finally as a typical case, Zhong Nanshan team led by the wechat public number "south mountain breathing" on the summary Discussion.

In addition to the hormone pulse therapy, Yuan Lingui could not meet her needs because of the strenuous inhalation of oxygen by ordinary nasal cannula. She also received Nasal high-flow oxygen therapy at the early stage of hospitalization. The concentration of inhaled oxygen was 60% , the flow rate increased gradually from 40lmin to 70lmin, and the patient received cefoperazone sodium and Sulbactam Sodium for anti inflammation, Welling for anti virus and other supportive treatment.

Xu Ying was impressed that she had suggested larger doses of the expectorant, Ambroxol, and the mucus dissolving drug. This recommendation is based on the discovery by the Guangzhou inhalation health institute that the small Airways of patients with new pneumonia form significant phlegm plugs. As a result, more than a week after hospitalization, Yuan Lingui coughed up a large amount of sputum, so that the medical staff was pleasantly surprised. Because one of the main symptoms of NCP is a dry cough, the ability to expel sputum indicates that lung function is improving.

Since February 16, the hospital has given yuan more traditional Chinese medicine consolidation therapy. On Feb. 17, Yuan's symptoms and laboratory tests improved markedly, and nasal high flow oxygen therapy was replaced by a lower oxygen flow mask, which was 98 percent Oxygenation. The nucleic acid of new coronavirus was negative on 20th and 22nd.

"Each case is a comprehensive treatment, there are dozens of treatment measures, each patient is not the same treatment program, " Chen Ailan stressed. In her view, Yuan Lingui treatment success, but also lies in the whole process of spiritual support.

Moral support is the easiest thing to overlook

Yuan Lingui just admitted to hospital, had refused all treatment measures, mood swings, oxygen consumption on the "Rub" to rise. Gao Jun still constantly encourage her, they have "from Hell to heaven, must insist, will be good" .

In fact, around that time, Gao was called into his office by his doctor and told that his mother's CT was not good and that she "should always be mentally prepared. ". Out of the doctor's office, he found a recliner and placed it next to Yuan Lingui's bed. He refused to be told to leave the room or to stay in the hallway as much as possible.

"I'm afraid I'll be sorry if she's gone and my relatives aren't around. " Gao held his mother's hand, but yuan was barely conscious at the time and couldn't respond, but he hoped her mother wouldn't be afraid.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Despite all the odds, Gauguin was willing to believe even the slightest chance. Because his eyes from time to time to emerge mother and son in the emergency room scene: "40-year-old, 60-year-old, fat, thin, tall, short, men and women have their own to give up, some family to give up, there are not the right way to comfort. "

He saw with his own eyes that some of the family members did not cooperate with the patient, desperate to use words to "provoke" each other. But usually irrelevant good-natured reminder, at this moment can instantly make the patient psychological collapse: "Once the collapse is very obvious, very fast, very fast. "

So he came up with a variety of ways to enlighten her: telling jokes, looking at family photos, watching videos with her family, and together with her imagination after the hospital life plan, encourage her to eat more. He also kept an eye on other patients, and if they improved, he immediately became a prime example of how he could inspire his mother. When his mother refused treatment, he would like to coax children, said: "If today played no effect, we do not play, try to see. "

Chaperone time is long and Drab, Gao Jun has not been idle down however. In addition to taking care of his mother, he kept watching the news on his mobile phone, trying to sum up the experience of treatment. "there seems to be no specific medicine, doctors can not do anything about it, the key is to improve the patient's immunity. "

He paid special attention to whether his mother wanted to drink water and eat. But when Yuan Lingui was sick, he couldn't swallow anything, his throat was full. He heard that injection albumin, Gamma Globulin can enhance human immunity, he also went to buy back.

Yuan Lingui watched his son 24-hour care unwilling to leave the hospital, such as physical recovery some, they began to force their own life self-care. She pretended to gulp down a meal and then went to fetch water and go to the toilet. "I was worried about what he would do if he got infected, " she said. "then I found out how I had deceived myself

"psychological communication with patients is the most important, sometimes more important than taking medicine, " Chen said. In nearly two decades of practice, she has found that psychological interventions are the most neglected of all stages of treatment, but have an irreplaceable energy.

Xu Ying would also urge other health care workers to encourage yuan, saying, "let's talk about the details and avoid talking about how sick we are all the time. " Thus, the most commonly used words among health care workers are: drink milk as water, eat well, sleep well, and feel good, you'll be better soon.

Gao remembers a male doctor wearing glasses who joked with his mother to encourage her to try to recover, otherwise the high-tech oxygen therapy machine he "snatched" for her would have been wasted. And I don't know how many times the doctors held mom's hand, even if a few words are full of encouragement.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Recently, Yuan Lingui heard that the Guangdong team may gradually withdraw, hiding in the toilet quietly cried. On March 5, she showed Chen, who was on rounds, how she could breathe through a straw in a Water Cup for eight seconds at a stretch. However, she also faces some difficulties, such as not completely deoxygenated, inability to chew, go to the toilet difficult squat, need to continue to receive rehabilitation treatment.

But the stone fell from her mind as her son left the hospital on February 22nd in intensive isolation, all negative for nucleic acid and without symptoms.

Gaojun thought, his mother and it is difficult to escape, but did not think that the final mother and son have become the fate of the beloved. On March 8, Gao returned home after 14 days of isolation to reunite with his long-lost wife and children. He most wanted to share with all the critically ill, critically ill patients and their families: "Don't give up. "
